attribute_definition: ID number associated with water system in the supplier service area. We created a lookup table to map DWR_ORG_ID and PWSID using the UWMP data. Note that there are some cases where the PWSID is NA and some cases where there are multiple PWSIDs.
Name of water system as reported in the eAR
DWR assigned ID number associated with the urban retail water supplier. UWMP data are reported by DWR_ORG_ID
Reporting start date which represents the first day of the month
Reporting end date which represents the last day of th month
Categorizes data by water produced or water delivered. Levels = c("water delivered", "water produced")

Type of water produced or delivered. Levels = c("other pws", "landscape irrigation", "agriculture", "single-family residential", 
"multi-family residential", "commercial/institutional", "other", 
"industrial", "groundwater wells", "non-potable (total excluded recycled)", 
"purchased or received from another pws", "recycled", "surface water", 
"sold to another pws", "non-potable water sold to another pws"
)
This is a calculated value that converts the quantity to acre feet.
